# Cross-Platform Standards

Read `docs/standards/engineering/cross-platform.md` before writing platform-specific code.

## Platform Guards

```c
#if defined(__APPLE__) && defined(__MACH__)   // macOS
#elif defined(_WIN32) || defined(_WIN64)      // Windows
#elif defined(__linux__)                       // Linux
#endif
```

Build-system flags for optional subsystems:
- `HU_GATEWAY_POSIX` -- fork/exec, signals, cron
- `HU_BUILD_WASM` -- WASM/WASI target
- `HU_ENABLE_CURL` -- libcurl HTTP client
- `HU_ENABLE_SQLITE` -- SQLite memory backend

## Rules

- New platform code MUST go through `platform.h` abstractions when possible
- Unsupported platforms return `HU_ERR_NOT_SUPPORTED` -- never silent no-ops
- Never hardcode `/tmp`, `~`, or `/bin/sh` -- use `hu_platform_get_*()` wrappers
- `HU_IS_TEST` bypasses side effects on ALL platforms
- Tests must pass on both macOS and Linux
